                          DarkWind Professions

    DarkWind has eleven professions. Herbalism, Mining, Skinning, Fishing,
and Forestry gather resources from the world. Alchemy, Leatherworking,
Smithing, Tailoring, Cybernetics, and Carpentry turn saved materials,
reagents, and equipment into useful outputs. Refining is a profession service.

Where to go:
  The profession building is 4e, n from Center of Town. It contains tools,
  craft rooms, workers, the work order board, and profession services.

Getting started:
  1. Go to the profession building and buy the tools you need.
  2. Use 'professions guide' for a practical first route.
  3. Gather materials with 'gather herbs', 'mine ore', 'skin corpse',
     'bait hook', 'fish', and 'chop tree'.
  4. Check saved materials with 'reagents' and source hints with
     'reagents search <item>'.
  5. Use 'professions craftable' or 'professions check ...' before
     crafting so you know what you are missing.

    Herbalism gathers herbs for potions, guildcraft, work orders, and
recipe cards. Mining gathers ore for bars, smithing, work orders, and
some guild preparations. Skinning gathers hides that become leather for
armor, bags, recipes, and guild preparations. Fishing catches food and
fish-part reagents used by recipes, guildcraft, and orders. Forestry uses a
forestry axe at marked Kingswood stands to save oak, ash, and pine timber in
standard through masterwork quality.

    Alchemy creates potions and recipe-card outputs. Leatherworking
creates hide and studded armor, converts hides to leather, and supports
crafted bags and utility recipes. Smithing creates metal armor and bars.
Tailoring creates padded armor and light clothing. Refining breaks old
equipment back into saved profession materials. Use 'set autorefine on' to
apply the same refining rules automatically to equipment from NPCs you kill.
Autorefine is mutually exclusive with autosell.

    Carpentry works in the Kingdom Commons or inside a homestead. It mills
timber into matching planks, crafts persistent placeable furniture, and makes
Framing Bundles required for every home upgrade after the hut. Use 'carpentry
list', 'reagents wood', 'help forestry', and 'help carpentry'.

Useful commands:
  professions
  professions guide
  professions gathering
  professions crafting
  professions craftable
  professions check <type> <target>
  reagents
  reagents search <item>
  workorders
  guildcraft list

    Work orders are posted in the profession building. They ask for saved
materials or crafted goods and reward coins, experience, profession
practice, shards, or recipe cards. See 'help workorders'.

    Profession-crafted gear can be improved with saved shards using
'inlay <crafted item> with <shard>'. See 'help inlays'.

    Guild members can use 'guildcraft' to spend saved profession materials
on guild-themed preparations. See 'help guildcraft'.

    Workers can be hired in the profession building for herbalism, mining,
skinning, fishing, and reagent scavenging. See 'help workers'.

    Skillups are determined by your skill and the tier of what you make.
Gathering professions always have a chance to improve, though the chance
gets lower at higher skill. Gathering skill also improves yield. When
manufacturing, lower-tier items stop giving skill once you outgrow them,
until you reach final-tier crafting.

